solutions.content:
**Approach**
- Take two pointers p and q at the head of linked list.
- Move q pointers by n to the right. Here n = 2.
- Then move both p and q pointers to right until q reaches the end.
- Then change pointer of p node to its next to next node.
- Don't forget to delete the last nth node.

**Digram Representation**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/295d90c6-c36f-48b5-a83a-7028b8640f4e_1664330424.1773272.png)

**C++ Code**

```cpp
ListNode* removeNthFromEnd(ListNode* head, int n) {
        ListNode *p = head, *q = head;
        while (n--) q = q->next;
        if (!q) return head->next;
        while (q->next) {
            p = p->next;
            q = q->next;
        }
        ListNode* toDelete = p->next;
        p->next = p->next->next;
        delete toDelete;
        return head;
}
```

