**Logical Thought**
The loop invariant is that two pointers `s, e` such that `s is always n nodes distance in front of e`. In this way, `s` is always the preceding node of the node to remove.When e is the `tail` node of the List (i.e. when `e.next = null`), we simply remove s.next (`s.next = s.next.next`). For example,
```
Given 1 - 2 - 3 - 4 - 5 - N, n = 2,
s is always 2 nodes distance in front of e
D - 1 - 2 - 3 - 4 - 5 - N
